===Noun===
'''waiting'''
# {{obsolete}} Watching, hence, an [[ogling]].
# The act of staying or remaining in [[expectation]].
# [[attendance|Attendance]], [[service]].

====Quotations====
* '''ca. 1393''': [[w:William Langland|William Langland]], ''[[s:Piers Plowman|Piers Plowman]]'', (C), iii. 94.
*: Al the lordshep of lecherye in lengthe and in brede,<br>As in workes and in wordes and '''waitynges''' of eyes.
* '''1871-72''': [[w:George Eliot|George Eliot]], ''Middlemarch'', xxxvi.
*: Green glasses for hock, and excellent waiting at table.
* '''1874''': [[w:John Fiske|John Fiske]], ''Outlines of Cosmic Philosophy'', I. 122.
*: In all ages, men have fought over words, without waiting to know what the words really signified.
* '''1876''': [[w:Richard Watson Gilder|Richard Watson Gilder]], ''The New Day, A Poem in Songs and Sonnets''
*: There was an awful waiting in the earth,<br>As if a mystery greatened to its birth.

